info.remarks:
Circumstances: found in July 1978 in ploughing; the field, previously pasture, had been ploughed for the first time in ‘years’; sword found caught up in cultivator, but finder was satisfied that it was turned up in particular part of field which showed a blackened rectangular surface discoloration—c. 25 x 35 yds.[;]
Typology: v.sl. bowed fg. cross section; ‘slot’ depressions around rivet holes; ricasso more-or-less flattened; hint of e. bev. below ricasso rapidly disappears; rounded loz. bl. section tending to renticular towards tip; rivet holes markedly bar-glass; remains of thin cg. Fl. within hilt slot; some likely porosity apparent on surfaces.[;]
Condition: hilt terminal broken off in antiquity; remainder broken in two—fracture […], therefore, recent. Prob. Due to find circumstances; whole length v. twisted & contorted—prob. Ancient, as are most of the edge dent and ‘tear’ low on bl. c.; small gouging just below shoulders gold—recent; also odd gold flecks along edges & small beven in one ricasso; v. tip blunted—ancient (& modern)[;]
Attached Material: scattered orange staining—apparently on surface—poss. adhering dust.[;]Landowner: Mr. Tinney, Matching Hall Farm
